title: The Patricians: or a candid examination into the merits of the principal speakers of the House of Lords. By the author of The Senators [i.e. T. H. Delamayne]

Four Poems, viz.: I. Armine and Elvira (a legendary tale in two parts by Mr Cartwright). II. The Hermit of Warkworth (a Northumberland ballad in three fits by T. Percy, Bishop of Dromore). III. The Deserted Village (a poem by Dr Goldsmith). IV. The Traveller (a poem by O. Goldsmith)
